🔐 Password Strength Checker (Python + Regex)

This is a simple yet effective password strength checker built in Python using regular expressions.  
It checks whether a password meets common security standards and provides instant feedback to the user.

---

✅ Features

- Checks if password is at least **8 characters** long  
- Verifies presence of:
  - Uppercase letters (A–Z)
  - Lowercase letters (a–z)
  - Digits (0–9)
  - Special characters (!@#$%^&*)

- Provides user-friendly output on whether the password is strong or weak

---

💻 Technologies Used

- Python 3.x  
- `re` module (Regular Expressions)  
- Command line interface (CLI)

---

🚀 How to Run

1. Clone the repository:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/password-checker.git
cd password-checker
